   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ House Republican leaders are whipping uneasy GOP
moderates into line to pass a massive $792 billion, 10-year tax cut
package. The president, for his part, is tendering $250 billion in
targeted cuts, itself risky. Maybe the parties will split the baby;
maybe not. Either way, the real game here is to strike poses for
next year's elections. (Tom Teepen is national correspondent for
Cox Newspapers.) MOVED MONDAY.
