<P>
   The Raytheon PRT 2000 transit system is the next best thing to
robot-driven taxis. In this system, small rail stations are spaced
about a third of a mile apart. An escalator whisks the rider up to
the elevated platform, where a vending machine sells tickets to
specific destinations. If a vehicle isn't already waiting at the
station, a central computer dispatches a single car to pick up the
passenger and as many as three companions. Talk about service!
Robert Kunzig, European Editor of Discover magazine, reports.
