President Clinton's decision to renew normal trade relations with
China for another year. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-PRIVACY (Washington) _ Senators and federal regulators
struggle over how to protect the privacy of Internet users from
companies that use new technologies to gather personal information
on consumers. Sen. Conrad Burns, R-Mont., has proposed legislation
that would give computer users more control over the collection and
distribution of such data. By MARK HELM.
</P>
