   POLITICAL NEWS (``p'') category
</P>
<P>
   HILLARY-CLINTON (Washington) _ First Lady Hillary Rodham Clinton
capitalizes on her role at the White House to press for causes
important to women, Jewish voters and the poor _ all important
constituencies in her exploratory New York Senate bid. By STEWART
M. POWELL. Story will also be filed in the WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'')
category.
</P>
<P>
   FEINSTEIN-VEEP (Washington) _ The name of Sen. Dianne Feinstein,
a California Democrat, is being floated in party circles as a
possible vice presidential running mate in the 2000 election, says
Sen. Ernest ``Fritz'' Hollings. By ERIC ROSENBERG and JUDY HOLLAND.
Story will also be filed in the WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'') category.
