<P>
   HOT (Kansas City, Mo.): Kansas City is in the grips of the
hottest heat wave since 1988, with the heat index last night never
dipping below 95 and today's temperatures expected to reach near
100 again _ and hit 104 by Friday. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Experts expect people to start dying very soon in KC as they are
in other parts of the Midwest. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   We fan out in the metro looking for the elderly without
air-conditioning; checking hosptials and MAST; updating electricity
consumption, etc. 30 inches. From staff reports. Photos. Story will
move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   APART (Kansas City, Mo.): Miraculously no one died in the fire
and natural gas explosion which leveled a Midtown apartment
building Monday evening. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Two critically injured Missouri Gas Energy workers are in the KU
Burn Unit and expected to recover while investigators comb through
the rubble looking for clues. We interview survivors of the blast,
perhaps even our own sports writer Jenni Carlson, who managed to
kick out a window to escape. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   We also check to see whether there were previous warnings about
natural gas problems and whether drought related. By KEVIN HOFFMAN.
25 inches. Photos. Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   MAYOR (Reeds Spring, Mo.): People in the small Ozarks town of
Reeds Spring, Mo. aren't sure whether their mayor, Joe Dan Dwyer,
is a child pornographer, or not. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   But that's what the federal government is accusing him of in
U.S. District Court in KC, not to mention witness tampering. It has
the townsfolk scratching their heads about what's going on in this
crazy world. By MATT SCHOFIELD. 365 inches. Photo. Story will move
in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   RIVER (Riverside, Mo.): A couple years ago the U.S. Postal
Service promised the tiny town of Riverside it could have its very
own zip code _ if it paid for a new post office.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   So the friendly folks of Riverside shelled out a couple million
to build the post office. But now the Postal Service says zip to a
new zip code and the friendly folks of Riverside are really upset.
By BILL GRAHAM. With photo. 30 inches. Story will move in the ``a''
category.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
