<P>
   ASTHMA CARE: Cases of the respiratory disease have more than
doubled in the past two decades, to 17.3 million, according to the
Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. To put a dent in such
statistics, numerous programs are knocking on patients' doors,
attempting to lesson frantic emergency room trips, reduce inpatient
hospital costs and improve quality of life. (Includes 4-column
color photo of boy using an inhaler.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: WHY ASTHMA: Modern life may be causing rise in number with
asthma.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: HEART PROCEDURE: A new laser procedure won't replace
conventional heart treatments, such as angioplasty and bypass
surgery, but it offers an option for patients with angina.
(Includes 2-column color photo of doctor next to a model of a
heart.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: NUTRITION GUIDELINES: The new Dietary Reference Intakes
from the Food and Nutrition Board of the National Academy of
Sciences will provide clearer guidelines for eating. (Includes
1-column color photo of nutritionist advising client.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: NUTRITION BOX: Four references of the Dietary Reference
Intakes explained.
</P>
