<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ The independent counsel law is dead
and Kenneth Starr is finally winding down, but the awful
consequences of the law go on. A major example is the legal pursuit
of former Housing Secretary Henry Cisneros. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
