</P>
<P>
   RUDY-ARKANSAS _ LITTLE ROCK, Ark. _ Coverage of New York Mayor
Rudy Giuliani's senatorial fund-raising efforts in Little Rock.
(Vejnoska, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-LATINOS _ WASHINGTON _ Gov. George W. Bush of Texas, who
declined an invitation by La Raza to speak at its national
convention this week, has also recently declined other invitations
to speak to Hispanic and other minority groups. The groups'
reaction and the possible political import. (Heath, Cox News
Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-EDUCATION _ AUSTIN, Texas _ As Gov. George W. Bush begins
to educate Americans on who he is and what he would do as
president, education will be on the top of the list. Texas is being
touted as a shining example of improvement, no small feat in the
country's second largest state, which used to rank near the bottom
in most academic indicators. Bush has made education a top
priority, from ending social promotion to increasing accountability
and testing to increasing state funding of public schools. But he's
been unable to deliver on vouchers, and some critics say he cannot
take credit for the recent rise. The seeds of Texas'success were
sown ini the mid-1980s, with laws to create smaller classes, give
more money to poor school districts and increase academic
standards. (Brooks, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   GORE-RUSSIA _ WASHINGTON _ Vice President Al Gore meets with
visiting Prime Minister Sergei Stepashin of Russia. The meeting
comes at a time of heightened diplomatic and military tensions
between the two powers. It also gives Gore a chance to burnish his
foreign policy credentials in the presidential race. (Shepard, Cox
News Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (i) international and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   NEW-TEACHERS _ WASHINGTON _ Nearly 10 percent of newly hired
teachers quit during their first year and must be replaced,
exacerbating teacher shortages. But that percentage falls when
districts create a formal support system for novice teachers, says
a study released Tuesday. (Mollison, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   OIL-ROYALTIES _ WASHINGTON _ A measure to protect oil companies
from paying higher royalties for oil drilled on public property
comes under attack Tuesday. Sen. Kay Bailey Hutchison, R-Texas, is
among the sponsors of a measure that would block new rules allowing
the higher royalties. (Malone, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   TOILETS _ WASHINGTON _ A House Commerce subcommittee holds a
hearing on a bill that would eliminate regulations requiring
low-flow toilets. (Dart, Cox News Service). 18.
</P>
