   By Lisa Stiffler. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   COPPER RIVER (CORDOVA, Alaska) _ The Copper River, renowned for
succulent salmon that create an annual frenzy in Seattle area
restuarants and supermarkets, has become the scene of Alaska's
latest environmental battle _ one that some believe could count the
salmon as its casualties. The latest skirmish over the large, muddy
river, will be fought Wednesday at a House hearing in Washington,
D.C.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story will move in the ``a'' and ``w''
categorie.)
</P>
<P>
   PIPELINE (WASHINGTON, D.C.) _ The federal agency responsible for
protecting the public from pipeline accidents is a failure, the
government's top safety official said Tuesday. National
Transportation Safety Board Chairman James Hall accused the Office
of Pipeline Safety of disregarding not only safety recommendations
from his agency, but also requirements imposed by Congress.
</P>
