June 8. The man, who has been booked 17 times for assaults and
other matters, was arrested Monday.
</P>
<P>
   By Vanessa Ho. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   RAMSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ On May 31, Forbes magazine ranked
Seattle as the No. 1 out of 162 cities in the United States for
business and careers. The magazine ranked Spokane, Wash., 161st,
behind only Johnson City, Tenn. This created hardly a stir in
Seattle. Spokane noticed. The leaders of the state's second-largest
city were irritated at being ranked with a town in the Appalachians
near the birthplace of Davy Crockett. They were even more irritated
at yet another disparaging comparison with Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   By Bruce Ramsey. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-MILLIONAIRE (PASADENA, Calif.) _ ``Who Wants To Be a
Millionaire'' is already a huge hit in Great Britain. Regis Philbin
thinks the quiz show will be a winner here, too, and he has signed
to host 13 installments airing nightly (except Aug. 23) from Aug.
16-29 at 8:30 on ABC.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story will move in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-DEEP (Undated) _ ``Deep Blue Sea'' is so broadly comedic
and filled with macho bluster that it's basically a cartoon, and
such a clumsy ripoff of ``Jaws'' and other, better films that it
often plays like a Zucker Brothers parody: ``Shark! _ the Movie.''
