as men to go on line. But despite their surging Internet savvy,
millions of women won't buy a computer unless a man helps choose
it, buy it and set it up, according to research by the American
Electronics Association. (Geroge Bridges/Cox News Service Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) ATLANTA, Ga. -- July 28, 1999 -- DESIGN-FRENCH-COX,
07-28 -- Mary Bairstow in her living room. The dust rarely settles
on Bairstow's furniture. One reason is that her Atlanta home serves
as a showroom/photo studio for many of the pieces she designs for
her small Atlanta home furnishings business. (Jean Shifrin/Cox News
Service Photo)
</P>
